						<div class="postbody">Thanks, blargg, I had one wich was accurate, but much more complicated, it needed 4 seeds and 4 temp registers.
<br />A good way to test the acuracy of a random number generator is to put the outpout to $4011, then call it again, etc... If you hear a noise wave, you're sure that it is accurate.
<br />Memblers, your trick isn't stupid at all. I think that Dragon Warrior does something like that on it's title screen.</div>

					
